        "summary": "Imam al-Sadiq (AS), transmitted via Malik ibn Anas, expresses amazement at two types of people: those who are stingy when worldly blessings come to them, and those who hoard when the world turns away. He teaches that generosity during prosperity causes no harm, while hoarding during adversity brings no benefit -- a profound lesson on detachment from the transient world.",
        "key_terms": {
